                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1679">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/697.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Minister of Nicaragua</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: Referring to our conversation of
                    to-day in regard to obtaining from Brown Brothers &amp; Company and Seligman
                    &amp; Company of New York, fifty thousand dollars ($50,000) for the use of your
                    Government, I would advise you that I have informed these bankers of the
                    contents of the memorandum which you left with me this morning, and of Mr.
                    Bryan’s autographic statement endorsed thereon. I enclose a copy of this paper
                    for your use.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
